organization_label (en): Tybee Island Light station and Museum
description (en): The Tybee Island Light Station is Georgia's tallest lighthouse with a history dating back to 1736. It stands at 145 feet tall and has three Light Keeper's Cottages nearby. Exhibits cover the Euchee tribe, history of Fort Screven, Tybee's Golden Era and more.

The Guard House was constructed by the United States Army to serve as the entrance to Fort Screven and the headquarters for soldiers who guarded the post. Today it is used as a community space where events are held.
